##  State Path Optimizations  ##

I noticed that providing `StateğŸ™Š` `.next` values as `Array`s and just manually removing duplicates was actually about twice as fast (running not very characteristic tests) as using `UniqueValueArray`, presumably because of Swift optimizing things and also not needing to persistently allocate as much memory.
Using `Set`s instead of `Array`s (and thus not preserving order) was about twice as fast again.

Because of this, Iâ€™ve allowed `.next` values to contain duplicates, deferring duplicate resolution to the actual parse step.
In addition, parsing simply uses an `Array` and a `Set` sideÂ·byÂ·side rather than a proper `UniqueValueArray`.
While I think `UniqueValueArray` is a valuable type in situations where being able to determine the index of an object in constant time is important, it is overkill for this application.

